critical points of acceleration and deceleration of the growth rate were not 
defined for these rats. Survival for RBD-groups decreased until 75 d of age and 
was unchanged between 75 and 450 d of life. From the 459 th d to the 589 th d of 
life deaths occurred successively. Controls survived until the 860 th d of life. 
Data point out the need for improving the basic food pattern of the region to 
prevent, among other things, a low life expectancy for the northeastern 
population.

