in the treatment of the essential trigeminal neuralgia is outstanding the 
patients satisfaction rate, which not only depends on pain relief and absence of 
recurrence, but also and very specially on the neurological deficiencies 
following the procedure. So, we consider that MVD is the most effective 
technique both in symptoms relief and neural functions and structures 
preservation, even though the possibility of appearance of complications 
following any major surgery.

